**Locating Files**

In the realm of digital game development, the ability to locate game files for any installed game is essential for effective asset management and utilization. Various methods can be employed to pinpoint the precise locations of game files. This includes leveraging a combination of Windows Registry entries, Game Store applications, or specific folders tailored to individual games. By tapping into these resources, digital creators can effortlessly identify and access the files associated with installed games, paving the way for seamless integration and manipulation of game assets.